review_blob: Cask, Shepley beer festival, creamy off white head, smooth hop aroma first taste is floral hop with good malt finish. Easy to sit and have a few

330 bottle from honest brew, pours dull, and hazy pretty flat, nice tropical note finishing but with hints of cider vinegar! Taste again like vinegar, pineapple leaving salty/tequila after taste, ended up in the sink!! Just not for me,
330 bottle from honest brew, crystal clear light golden, sparse head, strong Raw sourdough notes hints to light orange, strong bready taste with intense alcohol

330 bottle pours extremely lively, large bubbles, light haze, golden colour, citrus grapefruit aroma - hints at malt and yeast, slight tropical taste with hints of grapefruit finish in non assertive bitterness and slight yeast, but far to lively for me
beer_name: Mad Hatter Who Loves The Sun

review_blob: 330 bottle pours lively, typical us-05 characteristics, fruit golden raisin, plum and peach. Nice malty pineapple hints
beer_name: Wiper and True Amber Ale In The Groves

review_blob: 330 bottle, pour dark and thick syrup, tan head but disappeared fast, notes of toffee and light liquorice. Mouthfeel is smooth viscous, sticky and creamy, very light salt (Id like more) hints of coco, very nice Sunday dessert beer!
